.TH "hisi_acc_sg_buf_map_to_hw_sgl" 9 "hisi_acc_sg_buf_map_to_hw_sgl" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hisi_acc_sg_buf_map_to_hw_sgl \- Map a scatterlist to a hw sgl.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct hisi_acc_hw_sgl *" hisi_acc_sg_buf_map_to_hw_sgl
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist *sgl "  ","
.BI "struct hisi_acc_sgl_pool *pool "  ","
.BI "u32 index "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t *hw_sgl_dma "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
The device which hw sgl belongs to.
.IP "sgl" 12
Scatterlist which will be mapped to hw sgl.
.IP "pool" 12
Pool which hw sgl memory will be allocated in.
.IP "index" 12
Index of hisi_acc_hw_sgl in pool.
.IP "hw_sgl_dma" 12
The dma address of allocated hw sgl.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function builds hw sgl according input sgl, user can use hw_sgl_dma
as src/dst in its BD. Only support single hw sgl currently.
